<p>I want to hide a jQuery validator error message for a specific field. My current form is</p>  <pre><code>&lt;input type="text" name="userId" id="userId" class="required"&gt; &lt;input type="password" name="password" id="password" class="required"&gt; </code></pre>  <p>I'm using <code>$("div.error").hide();</code> to hide jQuery error messages. The code hides all of the error messages. but I want to hide only error message of password field.</p>  <p>Can we use <code>$("div.error #password").hide();</code>?</p>